name: Qucusaurus Chick
description:
A young Qucusaur with a light, agile body.
Its neck and wings have yet to fully develop, and it still has a long way to go before it can wield gaseous phlogiston. There are stories of older Qucusaurs pushing younglings off cliffs to encourage them to fly. While the truth of such tales is uncertain, as long as it keeps practicing day and night, there can be no doubt that the soft-feathered fledgling will eventually grow strong and resilient.

investigation.name: Natlan's Saurians
investigation.description: The Saurians that inhabit the land of Natlan.\nAccording to legend, more ancient dragons were better able to adapt to their environments, taking on different shapes and forms based on their surroundings. It is said that after losing their power, they were forced to become ever more dependent on their environments for survival, finally settling into the forms they still have as Saurians today.\nBut whether this is true or not, no one really knows.
